    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"夜里 carries different connotations in Chinese culture. While night can be associated with rest and\npeace, it's also traditionally seen as a time requiring caution. Chinese culture often emphasizes\nearly sleep and early rising, making 夜里 activities sometimes viewed as disrupting natural rhythms,\nthough modern urban life has changed these patterns significantly."}],"type":"paragraph"}
